Glucosyloxybenzyl 2 R -benzylmalate and glucosyloxybenzyl 2 R -isobutylmalate derivatives are structurally unique group of plant metabolites that occurs primarily in the family Orchidaceae . There are very limited studies reporting this class of compounds due to their rare occurrence in nature.
Arundina graminifolia D.Don Hochr. (Orchidaceae)
popularly known as bamboo orchid is widely distributed in subtropical Asia, particularly in South East Asian countries. It is a terrestrially growing orchid accepted as the only species in the genus (
;
). In China , the plant is found in Fujian , Yunnan , Zhejiang , Jiangxi , Guangdong and Sichuan provinces and it is popularly used as alone or in combination with other medicinal plants by the Bulang, Dai and Wa ethic groups. Traditionally,
A. graminifolia D.Don Hochr
is popular as an antidote for food and drug poisoning by the Dai ethnic group and it is one of the important ingredients found in several medicinal preparations because of the characteristic detoxification theory of the Dai ethnic group of “relieving before cure”. In addition,
A. graminifolia D.Don Hochr
is considered in Traditional Chinese Medicine as a drug that is effective for heat clearance, pain alleviation, eliminating wind and dampness (
). Furthermore, the roots/rhizomes and leaves of the plant are used for treating blood stasis and liver detoxification, pulmonary infection, beriberi edema, rheumatism, snakebites, traumatic injuries and as a skin moisturizer (
;
;
,
). This plant is known to be a rich source of bibenzyls (
;
